# <type>(<scope>): <subject>  (<= 72 chars, imperative mood)
#
# <body>  wrap at 72 chars. Explain the WHY, not the WHAT.
#
# <footer>
#   BREAKING CHANGE: <description>
#   Refs: #issue-id
#   Co-Authored-By: Name <email>
#
# ---- Conventional Commits reference ----
# Types:
#   feat      new feature
#   fix       bug fix
#   docs      documentation only
#   style     formatting, no code change
#   refactor  code change that neither fixes bug nor adds feature
#   perf      performance improvement
#   test      adding / fixing tests
#   build     build system, deps
#   ci        CI configuration
#   chore     misc, no src/test change
#   revert    revert previous commit
#
# Scopes (this repo):
#   web       Next.js app
#   agents    Python / LangGraph agents
#   db        Postgres / PostGIS schema, migrations
#   infra     docker-compose, deploy, VPS
#   ci        GitHub Actions, hooks
#   docs      README, plan, research, runbooks
#   deps      dependency bumps (with dependabot)
#
# Examples:
#   feat(agents): add glof detection graph node
#   fix(web): correct map bbox on mobile
#   chore(ci): bump pre-commit-hooks to v5
#   docs(infra): add restore drill to deploy runbook
#
# Rules:
#   - Subject: no trailing period, imperative ("add" not "added")
#   - One logical change per commit
#   - Body optional but recommended for non-trivial commits
